
[1]alliteration

   ALLITERA'TION, n. [L. ad and litera, a letter.]

   The repetition of the same letter at the beginning of two or more words
   immediately succeeding each other, or at short intervals; as f and g in
   the following line:

   Fields ever fresh, and groves forever green.
